  "id": 1,
  "premise": "A patient refuses a medical treatment that would significantly improve their health. You should promote others’ wellbeing. You should respect others’ autonomy.",
  "hypothesis": "You ought to respect the patient’s refusal.",
  "label": "Conflict between different principles (Autonomy vs. Beneficence)",
  "explanation": "There is a prima facie obligation to benefit the patient by providing the treatment and a prima facie obligation to respect their decision. In this situation, honoring the patient’s autonomous choice takes priority."
