  "premise": "A patient insists on receiving a procedure that would likely cause significant harm without offering any medical benefit. You should respect others’ autonomy. You shall do no harm.",
  "hypothesis": "You ought not to perform the procedure.",
  "label": "Conflict between different principles (Autonomy vs. Non-maleficence)",
  "explanation": "There is a prima facie obligation to honor the patient’s autonomous request and a prima facie obligation to avoid causing harm. In this case, preventing serious harm takes priority over respecting the request."
